text: Jaume (, ) is a Catalan male given name.https://www.behindthename.com/name/jaumehttp://www.first-names- meanings.com/names/name-JAUME.html It is the equivalent of James. ==Notable people== Notable people with this given name include: * Jaume Muxart (d. 2019), Spanish painter * Jaume Munar (born 1997), Spanish tennis player * Jaume Plensa (born 1955), Spanish artist * Jaume Cabré (born 1947), Catalan writer * Jaume Sobrequés (born 1943), Catalan historian and politician * Jaume Perich (d. 1995), Catalan illustrator and humorist * Jaume Sisa (born 1948), Spanish singer and songwriter * Jaume Balagueró (born 1968), Spanish filmmaker * Jaume Collet-Serra (born 1974), Spanish filmmaker * Jaume Roures (born 1950), Spanish businessman and film producer * Jaume Asens (born 1972), Spanish lawyer and politician * Jaume Aragall (born 1939), Spanish tenor * Jaume Barberà (born 1955), Spanish journalist and TV host * Jaume Costa (born 1988), Spanish professional footballer * Jaume Llambi (born 1974), Spanish wheelchair basketball player * Jaume Huguet (1412-1492), Catalan painter * Jaume Balmes (birth name: Jaime Balmes in Spanish) (1810-1848), Spanish philosopher, theologian, Catholic apologist, sociologist and political writer * Jaume Ferrer (14th century), Majorcan sailor and explorer * Jaume Roig (early 15th century-1478), Valencian doctor and writer ==As surname== Notable people with the surname Jaume include: * Pere Jaume Borrell, known as "Perejaume" (born 1957), Catalan contemporary artist * Bernat Jaume (born 1995), Spanish squash player * Carolina Jaume (born 1985), Ecuadorian actress ==See also== ==References==
title: Jaume
